AWKA – The son of the first Republic Senate President, Prince Ifeamuma Nwafor-Orizu has emerged the chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Nnewi North Local Government Area of Anambra. Prince Nwafor-Orizu on Saturday scored the highest number of votes to become the new chairman of PDP in the council area. He is the last son of the legendary Rt. Hon .Dr. A. A. Nwafor-Orizu. APC Chieftain Wants Election Dates Permanent In Nation’s… Philip Aivoji, Former Lagos Commissioner  Emerges Lagos State… In his acceptance speech, Prince Nwafor-Orizu thanked the party faithful for the confidence reposed in him and other members of his executive. He reassured them that the party under the new executive council will move PDP to a greater height and as well work assiduously to bring back all the members who have defected to other political parties back to the PDP fold. The youthful PDP chairman assured the numerous party loyalists that he would run a transparent and open door administration in which every member will be free to contribute their own quota in the management of the party. He praised the party’s firmer National Publicity Secretary Chief Olisa Metuh for insisting on due process and for also creating enabling environment for the youths to come on board as members of the executive. He said: “Under our watch, PDP will become a moving train and it is expected that all hands will be on the deck as we make PDP to become our dream political party. It is not a one man show, it is a collective responsibility.” Prince Ifeamuma declared. POLL In his comment, a stakeholder of PDP, Comrade Tempest Udeze congratulated the newly elected executives for emerging victorious in the local government Congress. Comrade Udeze said emphatically that the party faithfuls expect optimal performance from them. He also applauded the former National Publicity Secretary of PDP, Chief Olisa Metuh for ensuring that the right thing is done right in the council area.